records.label: Pre-Existing Condition 24/24
records.userValues: Pre-Existing Condition means any sickness or injury for which a Member received medical treatment, advice, care or services (including diagnostic measures) or took prescribed drugs within 24 months before the Member’s effective date of their program.

records.label: Specified Chronic Conditions
records.userValues: There is a 24 month waiting period before medical expenses for a pre-existing condition are eligible for sharing.

records.label: Cancer Limitations
records.userValues: Pre-exisiting or Recurring Cancer are not eligible for sharing

records.label: Medical Non-Compliance
records.userValues: Sharing for medical services will not be available when the conditions is shown to be the result of medical non-compliance with the Physician's recommended care, treatment or advice.

records.label: PPO Network
records.userValues: PHCS Network – Hospital Only

records.label: Out of Network
records.userValues: Using a Non-PPO provider is still the Member’s choice. The Non-PPO provider services can result in higher medical bills. Non-PPO Providers and Facilities may bill members for the difference between the bill charges and the program’s allowed amount.

records.label: Telemedicine
records.userValues: $0 Consult Fee (Dialcare) 24/7/365. Talk to a doctor by phone or online video to get a diagnosis, treatment options and prescription, if medically necessary.

records.label: Diagnostic / X-Ray / Labs
records.userValues: 100% after ISA; up to Maximum Limit Per Incident.

records.label: Specialists
records.userValues: 100% sharing after $75 Visit Fee due to an  Inpatient/Outpatient Surgery.

records.label: Outpatient Surgery
records.userValues: 90 day waiting period. After the ISA is met, eligible for sharing up to the Maximum Limit Per Incident. Life Threatening or Life Altering emergencies are immediately eligible for sharing.

records.label: Outpatient Therapy:Physical Therapy (PT), Occupational Therapy (OT), and Speech
records.userValues: If a condition is related to an eligible diagnosis, ordered by a Physician and performed by a licensed therapist, it is Eligible after the ISA is met. Up to a maximum of 20 visits combined visits per Incident.

records.label: Prescription Discounts

records.label: Inpatient Hospitalization
records.userValues: 100% after ISA up to Maximum Limit  Per Incident

records.label: Inpatient Surgery
records.userValues: 100% after ISA up to Maximum Limit  Per Incident

records.label: Guidelines
records.userValues: Medically necessary expenses that occur after your Effective Date. These are medical services from a health care provider which are eligible for sharing in accordance with the Membership Guidelines.

records.label: Waiting Period
records.userValues: Unless stated otherwise there is a 90 day waiting period for any medical expenses other than for accidents, injuries, or acute illnesses.

records.label: Ambulance
records.userValues: Land or air transportation for medically necessary emergency services to the nearest medical Facility or medical transportation between Facilities; when medically necessary, after the ISA is met, up to a Maximum Sharing of $10,000 per occurrence.

records.label: Emergency Room (ER)
records.userValues: $300 Visit Fee in/ out of network Emergency room services for a Life Threatening/Life Altering medical emergency provided on an Outpatient basis at a Hospital.

records.label: Emergency Room 24 hours or more (ER)
records.userValues: If at the Hospital for 24 hours or more, ER will be considered hospitalization and will apply to the ISA. In and Out of network sharing percentages will apply.
